Special_Criteria___Consideratio: Open to public, health care workers and first responders. Saline gargle test is available for adults and children (ages 4+).  See the children notes for how to prepare.
AcceptChildren: Yes. Saline gargle test available for children aged 4+. See website noted below to watch a video to see what is expected; the test is more successful when children have seen the video beforehand. If the sample cannot be collected successfully, a nasal swab is available as a backup.

Community_Collection_Center_Nam: Powell River Supported Self-Collection Testing Site
Specific_Location: Located at the 3rd floor parking lot of the Powell River General Hospital, accessed from Kiwanis Avenue near Willingdon Creek Village. Follow the signage from Joyce Avenue and look for the orange canister.
Days: Mon - Fri at the Testing Site. Testing is available at the Emergency Department outside of the hours below.
Special_Criteria___Consideratio: Appointment required. Fill out the form thru website below or call to request an appt. A saline gargle test kit will be available for pick up at your scheduled appt time. You can either complete the test in your vehicle on-site or inside the testing site.
Phone: 604-485-2028, available 09:00 - 14:00, Mon - Fri except stat holidays, to help with booking an appointment
AcceptChildren: 17 and under. Children under 4, and others who are not able to complete the saline gargle test will be tested through the Emergency Dept. If you are bringing a school-aged child to the supported self-testing clinic, please watch this video to prepare them. https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=ZvqjkbD-moA
